---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact / Request a Decode"
  description="Flag an error or request a new policy decode."
>
  <div class="container page-content prose">
    <h1>Contact / Request a Decode</h1>

    <h2>Found something out of date?</h2>
    <p>
      If a summary on this site no longer matches what the company's policy says, we want to
      know. Reader-flagged corrections go to the front of our review queue.
    </p>

    <h2>Want a policy we haven't decoded?</h2>
    <p>
      We're working through major retailers, subscription services, credit cards, and
      warranties. If there's a specific policy you'd like to see — yours or someone's you're
      considering — tell us.
    </p>

    <h2>How to reach us</h2>
    <p>
      For now, the simplest way is email:
      <strong>contact@fineprintdecoder.com</strong>
      <em>(coming soon — domain registration in progress)</em>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Include the company name and the policy you're asking about. If you're flagging a
      change, a link to the current version of the company's policy helps a lot.
    </p>

    <p class="placeholder-text" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      A proper contact form will replace this once the site is fully launched.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
